<div class="story">
    <div class="Title"><h2><span class="StoryLink"><span class="TitleSpan"><iframe src="http://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Frift.zam.com%2Fstory.html%3Fstory%3D27406&amp;layout=button_count&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=450&amp;action=like&amp;colorscheme=dark&amp;locale=en_US" scrolling="no" frameborder="0" class="fb-like" allowTransparency="true"></iframe>Discovery Log Parser Update at ZAM Rift! </span><span class="Byline"><span class="cont"><span title="4 days  ago">Aug 18th, 2011 at  2:03 PM</span> by <a href="/users/Calthine" class="BylineLink">Calthine</a></span></span></span></h2></div>
    <div class="Preview"><div class="cont"><div class="Buffer"></div><h3 class="Subhead">Now it's even easier to contribute to the best Rift database on the web!</h3><p>Since we unveiled our <a href="http://rift.zam.com/en/logparser.html">Rift discovery and combat log parser</a> players have uploaded over 6.5 million individual entries to the ZAM Rift maps and loot tables!  Thanks to <a href="http://rift.zam.com/story.html?story=27378">yesterday's hotfix</a> it just got even easier - no longer do players need to note the location of harvestables and artifacts, because Trion added them to the discovery log.</p>
<p>Follow <a href="http://rift.zam.com/en/logparser.html">the simple instructions</a> to painlessly upload your logs to ZAM Rift and you too can contribute to the wealth of information about the game!  When you upload the information from your discovery and combat logs it is immediately processed and applied instantly to our database.</p></div><div class="Buffer-bot"></div></div>
